The product is odd only if both dice show odd numbers (1, 3, or 5). The probability of getting an odd number on one die is $\frac{3}{6} = \frac{1}{2}$.

The probability that both dice are odd is

$$
\frac{1}{2}\times\frac{1}{2}
=
\frac{1}{4}
$$

The probability of an even product is the complement:

$$
1-\frac{1}{4}
=
\frac{3}{4}
$$

